title: Arsenal news: Arsene Wenger responds to Ian Wright claim over future | Metro News
text:
Chris Davie for Metro.co.uk Saturday 11 Feb 2017 4:28 pm Arsene Wenger insists he is ‘not ready to rest’. (Getty Images) 
Arsene Wenger insists he did not give any indication that his Arsenal future is coming to an end following Ian Wright’s claims on Friday evening. 
The ex-Gunners striker told BBC Five Live that he got the impression that the Frenchman would call time on reign at the end of the season after spending time with his former manger on Thursday night. 
Wenger’s current contract expires at the end of the season, although there are reports claiming that the 67-year-old. 
When asked about Wright’s feelings after Arsenal’s 2-0 win over Hull on Saturday, Wenger said: ‘I could be tired because I get up early in the morning and I finish late at night! 'I get the impression that that's it' 
Arsene Wenger has told Ian Wright that his time as #Arsenal ​ boss is coming to an end… pic.twitter.com/NXp4Tbzar1 
— BBC 5 live Sport (@5liveSport) February 10, 2017 
‘But I didn’t give any indication about my future.’ 
Asked if he was ever alone with Wright at one point in the evening, Wenger replied: ‘No, it was a question and answer with members of the diamond club, and that’s in the evening, there were many people there.
